- “Program” refers to any software, source code, or other work licensed
  under this Licence.

- “Commercial use” means any use of the Program that is intended for, directed
  toward, or reasonably expected to result in commercial advantage, monetary
  compensation, or other financial benefit, whether direct or indirect.

- “Non-commercial use” means private, educational, research, hobbyist, or
  community use that does not involve commercial advantage or monetary gain.

- “Public use” means making the Program available to users outside of the
  licensee’s private environment, including via websites, hosted services,
  servers, or networked applications.

